Package ball.http

Class ProtocolClient<P>

  • java.lang.Object
    • ball.http.ProtocolClient<P>
  • Type Parameters:
    P - The protocol type erasure.

    This class provides:

    1. HttpClient (client())
    2. HttpContext (context())
    3. A Proxy which implements the annotated protocol interface
    4. this implements HttpRequestInterceptor and HttpResponseInterceptor which are configured into HttpClientBuilder; subclasses can override process(HttpRequest,EntityDetails,HttpContext) and process(HttpResponse,EntityDetails,HttpContext)

    See the ProtocolRequestBuilder for the supported protocol interface Annotations and method parameter types.

    See ProtocolRequestBuilder and ProtocolInvocationHandler for a description of how HttpRequests are generated and executed.

    All Implemented Interfaces:
    HttpRequestInterceptor, HttpResponseInterceptor
    public abstract class ProtocolClient<P>
extends Object
implements HttpRequestInterceptor, HttpResponseInterceptor
    Abstract ProtocolClient base class.
    Author:
    Allen D. Ball
